          <td width="83%" class="lighttable">
            <br><P CLASS="post">
              Mages are horribly overpowered because of their spells like resist fire, resist ice, mana shield, and the fact that they get more AC just by adding points into widom and intelligence.  Warriors have to add strength to get a better weapon, and endurance for more armor (AC).  Agil and spells are totally optional.<br>Archers have to add agil and strength to get a bow, endurance so you can wear armor, wis/int for spells to get more AC because your endurance is so low and earthen strength because your strength sucks.  <br>Not only do archers have to add to every stat (sure, you could go around in studded leather and without spells, I wouldn't recommend it though)  but there is an incredible lack of items for archers...  Mages get rings that are 5 ac and 25 int, ac and +15 to all stats, necklace thats 10 ac and 10 to all stats, shields that are AC and a + to stats (that eye of the tiger thing)  tons of robes, and a one handed staff thats +50 int to top it all off.  Warriors get their standard weapons/armor, and rings that cast spells that will raise their str/attack, a hero's amulet that i don't even know what it does, 4 or 5 bracelets that are 10 ac (take ur pick).  What exactly is there in the game for archers?  Theres a robe, a couple rings...  oh, and bows.  Final score, Mages 38, warriors 15, archers -5.  Vircom wouldn't know what balance is if it jumped out and bit them.  When are archers gonna get some decent stuff?  (And whats up with those seraph only no-drop capes?  Duh.... earth to Vircom)<br><br>
            <br><br>
          </td>
