          <td width="83%" class="lighttable">
            <br><P CLASS="post">
              Well, I read through this, and I was here before the changes. Not as long as some of you, but pretty long. I have always thought that the game seemed unbalanced before SH. It appeared that warriors had the advantage. I see that some are complaining that now mages can Kick bootie due to the colloseum, but how does that make the game unbalanced? And, if someone can level fast how does that make it unbalanced? <br><br>My points: <br><br>Seraphing is equal to all players. So, all players have the opportunity to rebuild their characters and add attributes of mage or warrior..or whatever. That is equal to all. So, the warriors that are getting "spanked" in the colloseum could either seraph and add mage power or maybe go in with mages? (granted, I just seraphed and have not dipped a toe into the colloseum, so I'm not quite sure how it works yet)<br><br>Also, the leveling frenzy...well, I think it rocks. I love the harder monsters and the greater possibility to level and grow stronger...There is much more to explore and it's not a tedious, draining process to get experience. We all wanted to get more experience, right? And, it doesn't make the game unbalanced that now some people who are newer are getting stronger fast. It just means that the older players need to stay on the ball and put in equal time. It seems to me that the game has become more balanced because it allows us all the possibility to become strong, high levels, and to seraph adding unique features and trying out new aspects of the game. I'm for it.  imho..<br><br><br><br>
